1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill No. 2989, Pages 17-18, Section 313.435,
2 Lines 1-27, by deleting all of said section and lines and inserting in lieu thereof the following:
3
4 "313.435. 1. A municipality shall adopt an ordinance authorizing video lottery game
5 terminals within the corporate limits of such municipality. Such municipality shall notify the
6 commission of the ordinance within seven days of passage.
7 2. A county commission shall, for the unincorporated area of the county, adopt an
8 ordinance authorizing video lottery game terminals within the unincorporated area of the county.
9 Such county shall notify the commission of the ordinance within seven days of passage.
10 3. Any municipality or county adopting an ordinance that authorizes the licensing of
11 video lottery games shall notify the commission of such action and provide a certified copy of
12 such ordinance to the commission. Upon receiving such notification and ordinance, the
13 commission shall license video lottery game retailers within such area covered by such
14 municipal or county ordinance."; and
15
16 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
17 accordingly.
